This list is structured by platform sections so you can use it later for database planning, API endpoints, or feature documentation.
---
## USER & ACCOUNT FUNCTIONS
1. **Function of creating an account** — Allows a new user to sign up using email, phone number, or student ID.
2. **Function of logging in/out** — Authenticates and securely logs the user in or out of the system.
3. **Function of resetting password** — Sends recovery email or OTP for forgotten passwords.
4. **Function of editing profile** — Enables updating name, bio, avatar, education, and personal info.
5. **Function of verifying user identity** — Confirms identity via student email or document upload.
6. **Function of deleting account** — Permanently removes the user profile and data.
7. **Function of setting privacy preferences** — Controls visibility of profile, posts, and contact info.
8. **Function of deactivating account** — Temporarily hides account without deletion.
9. **Function of managing notifications** — Lets users enable, disable, or mute specific alerts.
10. **Function of reporting bugs or feedback** — Sends app feedback or issue reports to admin.
---
##  SOCIAL & CONNECTION FUNCTIONS
11. **Function of adding friends** — Sends and accepts friend requests.
12. **Function of following users** — Allows one-way following of public accounts or creators.
13. **Function of recommending friends** — Suggests users based on mutual friends, classes, or location.
14. **Function of blocking or unblocking users** — Restricts communication and visibility.
15. **Function of viewing profiles** — Displays another user’s details, photos, and posts.
16. **Function of viewing mutual friends** — Shows shared connections between two users.
17. **Function of tagging friends** — Allows mentioning users in posts, photos, or comments.
18. **Function of inviting friends** — Sends invites via link, email, or QR code.
---
## POSTS, FEED & REACTION FUNCTIONS
19. **Function of creating a post** — Publish text, image, or video content.
20. **Function of editing or deleting a post** — Modify or remove previously shared content.
21. **Function of liking and reacting** — Express emotions through various reaction types.
22. **Function of commenting on posts** — Add opinions, questions, or discussions.
23. **Function of sharing posts** — Repost content on your timeline or via messages.
24. **Function of saving posts** — Bookmark posts for later reading.
25. **Function of viewing feeds** — Loads personalized or trending content from friends and groups.
26. **Function of reporting a post** — Flags inappropriate content for moderation.
27. **Function of filtering feed** — Sort feed by trending, following, or topic interests.
---
##  MESSAGING & INTERACTION FUNCTIONS
28. **Function of sending messages** — Send text, images, or files to friends or groups.
29. **Function of creating group chats** — Start and manage multiple-member conversations.
30. **Function of making voice or video calls** — Real-time communication between users.
31. **Function of sending voice notes** — Send recorded audio messages.
32. **Function of reacting to messages** — Add emojis or quick responses in chats.
33. **Function of deleting or editing messages** — Remove or correct messages.
34. **Function of seeing online status** — Show active or last seen time.
35. **Function of typing indicators** — Display when someone is typing.
---
## STUDY & EDUCATION FUNCTIONS
36. **Function of AI study buddy** — Provides tutoring, answers, or explanations using AI.
37. **Function of searching for study materials** — Find notes, past papers, or resources.
38. **Function of uploading academic content** — Share notes, presentations, or tutorials.
39. **Function of creating study rooms** — Virtual collaboration rooms for group learning.
40. **Function of scheduling study sessions** — Set reminders or events for learning.
41. **Function of joining peer tutoring sessions** — Connect with other students for help.
42. **Function of accessing leaderboards** — Displays rankings or progress points.
43. **Function of taking online quizzes or tests** — Practice questions and instant results.
44. **Function of AI content summarization** — Auto-summarizes lessons or notes.
45. **Function of resource recommendation** — Suggests new materials or topics to study.
---
##  MEDIA, STORIES & ENTERTAINMENT FUNCTIONS
46. **Function of creating stories or reels** — Upload short videos or pictures with music.
47. **Function of viewing stories** — Browse friends’ daily stories.
48. **Function of liking or reacting to reels** — Engage with short-form video content.
49. **Function of watching long videos** — Stream educational or entertainment videos.
50. **Function of subscribing to creators** — Follow creators for exclusive updates.
51. **Function of live streaming** — Broadcast real-time video sessions or classes.
52. **Function of donating during streams** — Send monetary support to creators.
